The Indian navy searched for aborigines on the Nicobar islands to prevent their extinction.
The Shompen tribe resides in Campbell Bay, surrounded by mangroves.
The Andamanese, already endangered, live on Strait Island.
The tsunami caused severe damage to coral reefs and marine life.
Mangroves and coral reefs act as natural shields against tsunamis.
The destruction of mangroves and coral reefs worsened the impact of the tsunami.
Efforts are being made to rehabilitate damaged mangroves and assess environmental damage.
The focus is on human casualties, but marine ecosystems also suffered significant losses.
